<TITLE> Death count rises to 3,199 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, Nov 22 (bdnews24.com)  The death toll from mega-cyclone Sidr reached 3,199 with 1,046 missing at 4pm Thursday, the army said at a regular news briefing. Lt Col Main Ullah Chowdhury of the Armed Forces Division said relief and rehabilitation operations were at full throttle in the cyclone-hit areas. Chowdhury said the army was giving out relief supplies in 15 affected districts and coordinated the relief operations of governmental, semi-governmental and non-governmental organisations. On Thursday 59.6 tonnes of relief materials had been sent from Dhaka to the affected areas, he told reporters, adding 204 tonnes of rice had so far been sent. Pakistan had sent two cargo planes with relief and would send a mobile hospital to treat the survivors by Friday morning. Major Emdad said the army had installed six water purification plants in the vulnerable areas. He said the army had asked people to send money to account No. 02-0310197069 opened in the principal branch of Trust Bank. "We have got huge response," Emdad added. bdnew
